# DecompGTI — Implementation Walkthrough

## What Was Built

All new files were created **alongside** the existing `GraphInstruct/` folder. Nothing in `GraphInstruct/` was moved, deleted, or modified.

## New Files Created

### 📊 Evaluation Framework (`evaluation/`)
| File | Purpose |
|------|---------|
| [metrics.py](file:///home/ramji.purwar/DecompGTI/DecompGTI/evaluation/metrics.py) | 5 evaluation metrics: JSON validity, tool accuracy, parameter F1, adjacency F1, task success rate. Includes `AggregateMetrics` class with per-size and per-task breakdowns. |
| [benchmarks.py](file:///home/ramji.purwar/DecompGTI/DecompGTI/evaluation/benchmarks.py) | Test set generator. Creates graphs using networkx with known ground-truth answers. Supports 8 task types × 4 sizes (mini/small/medium/large). |

### 📝 Scripts (`scripts/`)
| File | Purpose |
|------|---------|
| [evaluate.py](file:///home/ramji.purwar/DecompGTI/DecompGTI/scripts/evaluate.py) | Main evaluation runner. Loads model → runs inference on test set → parses output → executes tools → computes metrics → prints report. Supports pre-saved predictions for GPU-free re-evaluation. |
| [compare_baselines.py](file:///home/ramji.purwar/DecompGTI/DecompGTI/scripts/compare_baselines.py) | Baseline comparison against base Qwen (zero-shot), GPT-4o (API), and Claude (API). Uses same metrics for fair comparison. |

### 🌐 Web Demo (`web/`)
| File | Purpose |
|------|---------|
| [app.py](file:///home/ramji.purwar/DecompGTI/DecompGTI/web/app.py) | Gradio web demo. Shows the 3-step decomposition pipeline interactively. **Zero config options** for users — all inference params baked into YAML configs. Has example buttons for quick testing. |

